README.Info:
This file contains the projection of the XENONnT nuclear recoil binwise approximate likelihood,
allowing recasts of the XENONnT NR sensetivity. Please cite: 
cite info here

Xedges.info: Edges in true nuclear recoil energy [keV] used in the migration matrix
Xedges.title: True NR recoil energy

Yedges.info: Edges in reconstructed nuclear recoil energy [keV] used in the migration matrix
Yedges.title: Reconstructed NR recoil energy

Z.info: Migration matrix from true energy (first axis) to reconstructed energy (second axis) expressed as probability of an event in a certain true energy bin ending up in a certain reconstructed energy bin. This includes both dispersion and efficiency, so the probabilities in a given true energy bin sum up to the efficiency
Z.title: Transfer Probability
